SET
    course_description = '<div class="richtext richtext__medium"> <div class="lede">Unlock the power of your imagination and shape the world through art.</div><p>If you see the world as a place full of possibility, where ideas spark change and beauty tells a story, then the Bachelor of Fine Arts is the perfect space for you to grow. At the University of Tasmania, you''ll be encouraged to explore, experiment, and express your unique perspective through art.</p><p>Tasmania is a place where creativity thrives. It''s a landscape shaped by nature and culture, history and innovation, industry and imagination. Here, you''ll find inspiration in every corner, from the wild coastlines to the vibrant arts communities.</p><p>Whether you''re passionate about a single discipline or excited to explore multiple mediums, you''ll be supported to develop your artistic voice and build a fulfilling creative career. Our Fine Arts degree combines hands-on studio practice with critical thinking, helping you create work that resonates, challenges, and transforms.</p><p>Complete a major in either Studio Practice or Theatre and Performance.</p><p>Choose from specialised studios in:</p><ul><li><strong>Drawing and Printmaking</strong></li><li><strong>Painting</strong></li><li><strong>Photography</strong></li><li><strong>Object and Furniture</strong></li><li><strong>Sculpture and Time-Based Media</strong></li></ul><p>In the <strong><a href="https://www.utas.edu.au/study/undergraduate/theatre-and-performance">Theatre and Performance major</a> </strong>you can select from:</p><ul><li>Performance skills 1 &amp; 2</li><li>The theatre machine</li><li>Playing texts</li><li>Experimental production and directed theatre project</li><li>Global media and cybertheatres</li><li>Writing for performance</li><li>Directed theatre project</li></ul><p>When you undertake the Bachelor of Fine Arts you''ll complete two Creative Curriculum units.</p><p>Each studio offers a progression from foundational skills to advanced practice, supported by our dynamic Critical Practice units that sharpen your conceptual thinking and creative resilience.</p><p>This degree can be combined to combined to form a double degree. Study what you want, <a href="https://www.utas.edu.au/study/undergraduate/double-degrees">explore your options</a> and find out how you can accelerate your career.</p> </div>',
    total_course_duration = 'Minimum 3 years, up to a maximum of 7 years.',
    offshore_tuition_fee = '120583',
    entry_requirements = '<div class="accordion--content"> <p>All international students will need to meet the minimum English Language Requirements, University General Entry Requirements and any course specific requirements such as pre-requisite subjects, if applicable.</p> <p><strong>English Language Requirements</strong></p> <p>This degree requires an IELTS (Academic) of 6.0, with no individual band less than 5.5, or a PTE Academic score of 50, with no score lower than 42 or equivalent.</p> <p>For students who do not meet the English Language Requirement through citizenship or prior studies in English in an approved country, evidence of an approved English language test completed within the last 2 years must be provided. See the <a href="https://www.utas.edu.au/international/applying/entry-requirements/english-language-requirements">English Language Requirements</a> page for more information.</p> <p><strong>General Entry Requirements</strong></p> <p>Admission to undergraduate courses at the University of Tasmania requires the completion of qualifications equivalent to a 12th year of education in Australia.</p> <p>Please review the <a href="https://www.utas.edu.au/international/applying/entry-requirements/equivalent-undergraduate-entry-requirements-by-country">equivalent undergraduate entry requirements</a> to see the minimum requirement relevant to your country. The ATAR information for this course is located in the “For Domestic Students” section of the entry requirements on this page.</p> <p>You can also meet the General Entry Requirement for this course with the following qualifications or prior studies:</p> <ul> <li>Completion of an equivalent AQF Certificate IV or above</li> <li>Complete or incomplete (minimum 25 credit points) of previous tertiary study at Bachelor level or higher</li> <li>You may also be required to submit a portfolio and statement if your previous studies are not in a related field.</li> </ul> <p>If you do not meet the minimum requirements, we offer the <a href="https://www.utas.edu.au/courses/acad/courses/x0f-foundation-studies-program-standard">Foundation Studies Program.</a></p> <p><strong>Course Specific Requirements</strong></p> <p>To be an eligible for an offer, you must have studies or experience equivalent to a satisfactory achievement in one of the following Tasmanian Senior Secondary subjects:</p> <table border="1"> <tbody> <tr> <td> <p>ART315117</p> </td> <td> <p>Art Production</p> </td> </tr> <tr> <td> <p>ART315214</p> </td> <td> <p>Art Studio Practice</p> </td> </tr> <tr> <td> <p>ARA315116</p> </td> <td> <p>Art Theory and Criticism (replaces Art Appreciation ARA315111)</p> </td> </tr> <tr> <td> <p>CGD315118</p> </td> <td> <p>Computer Graphics and Design</p> </td> </tr> <tr> <td> <p>HDS315118</p> </td> <td> <p>Housing and Design</p> </td> </tr> <tr> <td> <p>MED315117</p> </td> <td> <p>Media Production</p> </td> </tr> <tr> <td>SDD315120</td> <td>Drama</td> </tr> <tr> <td>SDP315120</td> <td>Theatre Performance</td> </tr> <tr> <td> <p>TEG315115</p> </td> <td> <p>Technical Graphics</p> </td> </tr> </tbody> </table> <p>You can <a href="https://faq.utas.edu.au/app/online_enquiry/seedData/53g-bachelor-of-laboratory-medicine">enquire online</a> for information on interstate and international equivalents to the Tasmanian senior secondary subject above. If you have not met this prerequisite, you will need to complete a UTAS <a href="https://www.utas.edu.au/foundation-units">foundation unit</a> before you start your course.</p> </div>',
