SET
    course_description = '<div class="richtext richtext__medium"> <div class="lede">The Bachelor of Arts is the ultimate, flexible university degree, and you can tailor it to explore your interests and discover a wide range of career possibilities. It is an opportunity to pursue what you loved in high school or branch out into areas you''ve never had the opportunity to explore.</div><p>Our students embrace the joy of open enquiry, are curious about life’s big questions, and are on a life-long quest for knowledge and inspiration. You will hone skills like critical-thinking, research, and inter-cultural awareness under the guidance of passionate academics who are leading researchers in their fields.</p><p>You can take on cultural, environmental, and humanitarian challenges from multiple perspectives and gain the confidence to make a positive difference. Through our close relationships with government and industry partners, we will prepare you to start your career with the skills employers want.</p><p>We''ve identified six core passions that may resonate with your aspirations for the future:</p><ol><li><strong>Making sense of critical global issues</strong> - Chinese, Gender and Diversity, Politics and Policy, Sociology, and Sustainability</li><li><strong>Interpret the world through arts and culture</strong> - Ancient languages, Classics, Creative Arts and Health, German, History, and Japanese</li><li><strong>Support and empower people</strong> - <a href="https://www.utas.edu.au/study/undergraduate/theatre-and-performance" title="Theatre and Performance">Theatre and Performance</a>, Criminology, Philosophy, Gender and Diversity, and Psychological Science</li><li><strong>Contribute to a just society </strong>- Criminology, Gender and Diversity, International Relations, Philosophy, and Geography and Environment</li><li><strong>Develop intercultural connections</strong> - Ancient languages, Chinese, English and Writing, Indonesian, Media and Communication and History</li><li><strong>See the past to shape the future</strong> - Creative Arts and Health, Criminology, Gender and Diversity, Philosophy and Sociology</li></ol><p>The Bachelor of Arts is one of the most versatile to pair with other degrees to create a double degree. One of the most popular is the Bachelor of Arts with a Master of Teaching or a Bachelor of Arts with a Master of Strategic Communication. There are many other options, choose what you want to study. <a href="https://www.utas.edu.au/study/undergraduate/double-degrees">Explore your options</a> and find out how you can accelerate your career.</p> </div>',
