    course_description = '<div class="richtext richtext__medium"> <div class="lede">Your career in Laboratory Medicine starts here</div><p>Laboratory Medicine is at the heart of modern healthcare. Almost every diagnosis depends on accurate laboratory results, and skilled professionals are needed to deliver them.</p><p>The Master of Laboratory Medicine prepares you to join this essential field with the right mix of theory and hands-on experience. In this practical, industry-focussed course you will study:</p><ul><li>Clinical chemistry</li><li>Haematology</li><li>Microbiology</li><li>Histopathology</li><li>Blood transfusion science</li><li>Molecular biology and more</li></ul><p>Each subject includes practical lab sessions, averaging three hours per unit per week, building real-world skills that employers value.</p><p>In your final semester, you will complete a 16-week Professional Experience Placement in an Australian laboratory. We help you find a placement that fits your goals, and many students are offered jobs by their host organisations before graduating.</p><p>This course attracts students from around the world. You will be part of a diverse and supportive community, with small classes and approachable teaching staff committed to your success.</p><p>In 2024, students rated the course:</p><ul><li>100% for peer engagement, learning resources, and student support*</li><li>Over 90% for teaching quality and skills development*</li></ul><p>Graduates are in demand across hospitals, private labs, research centres, and public health. Starting salaries are strong, and the career opportunities are wide-ranging. Take your next step with confidence and join a course that prepares you for a meaningful and rewarding career.</p><p><strong>Are you interested in laboratory medicine but don''t yet have an undergraduate degree?</strong> We offer a four-year combined <a href="https://www.utas.edu.au/study/undergraduate/biomedicine" title="Biomedicine">Bachelor of Biomedicine/Master 