    course_description = '<div class="richtext richtext__medium"> <div class="lede"><strong>Architecture develops ideas and forms that enrich experience and imagination with reference to environmental, social, and economic realities.</strong></div><p>Our course fosters innovation in design, addressing today’s environmental and social challenges. Experience hands-on learning with a focus on community impact and creative freedom. We offer design studios rooted in our island’s natural beauty and heritage. Our 25-year tradition of Learning-By-Making shapes our curriculum, and our collaborative studios and workshops encourage creative exploration. Prepare for a future in architectural practice with our project-based approach.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p style="font-weight: bold;">Catalyst Program</p><p>Want to combine your degree with overseas trips, summer research programs, scholarships and special events? Our Catalyst Program offers domestic high achieving school leavers all this and more.</p><p>All domestic students with an ATAR of 90 or greater, enrolled in a range of STEM courses will be awarded a $3,000 Catalyst Scholarship. Across the program students can access scholarships of up to $14,500 in value, and gain experience that will make you stand out in your chosen field. <a href="https://www.utas.edu.au/study/catalyst-program">Learn more about the Catalyst Program</a></p> </div>',
